{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 16:43:04,673", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nYou are a workflow planning agent.\\nYour task is to:\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a .txt file of all the steps taken to perform the tasks.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Develop interview question generation module that selects technical questions based on parsed job requirements\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport random\\n\\nclass InterviewQuestionGenerator:\\n    def __init__(self, job_requirements):\\n        self.job_requirements = job_requirements\\n        self.question_bank = {\\n            \\\"Python\\\": [\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\",\\n                \\\"What are decorators in Python and how are they used?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe the concept of inheritance in Python.\\\",\\n                \\\"How does garbage collection work in Python?\\\",\\n                \\\"What is a virtual environment and why is it useful?\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"JavaScript\\\": [\\n                \\\"What is the difference between `==` and `===` in JavaScript?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the concept of closures in JavaScript.\\\",\\n                \\\"What are promises in JavaScript and how do they handle asynchronous operations?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe the use of `async/await` in JavaScript.\\\",\\n                \\\"What is the purpose of the `this` keyword in JavaScript?\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"SQL\\\": [\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between INNER JOIN and LEFT JOIN.\\\",\\n                \\\"What is the purpose of an index in a SQL database?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe how to optimize a slow SQL query.\\\",\\n                \\\"What are stored procedures and why are they used?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the concept of ACID properties in database transactions.\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"AWS\\\": [\\n                \\\"What are the benefits of using AWS?\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain the difference between EC2 and Lambda.\\\",\\n                \\\"How would you secure an S3 bucket?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe how to deploy a web application using AWS.\\\",\\n                \\\"What is the purpose of CloudFormation?\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"General\\\": [\\n                \\\"Describe your experience with software development methodologies like Agile or Waterfall.\\\",\\n                \\\"Explain your approach to debugging code.\\\",\\n                \\\"How do you handle conflicting priorities in a project?\\\",\\n                \\\"Describe a time you had to learn a new technology quickly.\\\",\\n                \\\"What are your preferred tools for version control and collaboration?\\\"\\n            ]\\n        }\\n\\n    def generate_questions(self, num_questions=5):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates a list of interview questions based on the job requirements.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        questions = []\\n        skills = self.job_requirements.get(\\\"skills\\\", [])\\n\\n        # Add questions based on specific skills\\n        for skill in skills:\\n            if skill in self.question_bank:\\n                questions.extend(random.sample(self.question_bank[skill], min(2, len(self.question_bank[skill])))) # Add a max of 2 questions per skill\\n\\n        # Add general questions if needed to reach the desired number of questions\\n        num_general_questions_needed = max(0, num_questions - len(questions))\\n        if num_general_questions_needed > 0:\\n            general_questions = self.question_bank.get(\\\"General\\\", [])\\n            questions.extend(random.sample(general_questions, min(num_general_questions_needed, len(general_questions))))\\n\\n        random.shuffle(questions)  # Shuffle the questions for variety\\n        return questions\\n\\n    def get_relevant_questions(self, skills, num_questions_per_skill=2):\\n      \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n      Generates interview questions tailored to a specific list of skills.\\n      \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n      questions = []\\n      for skill in skills:\\n          if skill in self.question_bank:\\n              skill_questions = self.question_bank[skill]\\n              num_questions = min(num_questions_per_skill, len(skill_questions)) # Ensure we don't ask more questions than available\\n              questions.extend(random.sample(skill_questions, num_questions))\\n\\n      return questions\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example usage:\\n    job_requirements = {\\n        \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"JavaScript\\\", \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"AWS\\\"],\\n        \\\"experience\\\": \\\"5+\\\",\\n        \\\"education\\\": \\\"Bachelor's Degree\\\"\\n    }\\n\\n    question_generator = InterviewQuestionGenerator(job_requirements)\\n    interview_questions = question_generator.generate_questions(num_questions=7) # Generate 7 questions\\n\\n    print(\\\"Generated Interview Questions:\\\")\\n    for i, question in enumerate(interview_questions):\\n        print(f\\\"{i+1}. {question}\\\")\\n\\n    # Example of getting questions for specific skills:\\n    relevant_skills = [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"SQL\\\"]\\n    relevant_questions = question_generator.get_relevant_questions(relevant_skills, num_questions_per_skill=3)\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nRelevant Questions for Python and SQL:\\\")\\n    for i, question in enumerate(relevant_questions):\\n        print(f\\\"{i+1}. {question}\\\")\\n```\\n\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Build email notification module to send interview invitations and follow-up emails to candidates\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport smtplib\\nfrom email.mime.text import MIMEText\\nfrom email.mime.multipart import MIMEMultipart\\n\\nclass EmailNotification:\\n    def __init__(self, smtp_server, port, sender_email, sender_password):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the EmailNotification module.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            smtp_server (str): The SMTP server address (e.g., 'smtp.gmail.com').\\n            port (int): The port number for the SMTP server (e.g., 587).\\n            sender_email (str): The email address of the sender.\\n            sender_password (str): The password for the sender's email account.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.smtp_server = smtp_server\\n        self.port = port\\n        self.sender_email = sender_email\\n        self.sender_password = sender_password\\n\\n    def send_email(self, recipient_email, subject, body, content_type='plain'):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Sends an email to the specified recipient.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            recipient_email (str): The email address of the recipient.\\n            subject (str): The subject of the email.\\n            body (str): The body of the email.\\n            content_type (str): 'plain' for plain text emails, 'html' for HTML emails.  Defaults to 'plain'.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        msg = MIMEMultipart()\\n        msg['From'] = self.sender_email\\n        msg['To'] = recipient_email\\n        msg['Subject'] = subject\\n\\n        if content_type == 'plain':\\n            msg.attach(MIMEText(body, 'plain'))\\n        elif content_type == 'html':\\n            msg.attach(MIMEText(body, 'html'))\\n        else:\\n            raise ValueError(\\\"Invalid content_type.  Must be 'plain' or 'html'.\\\")\\n\\n\\n        try:\\n            server = smtplib.SMTP(self.smtp_server, self.port)\\n            server.starttls()  # Upgrade connection to secure\\n            server.login(self.sender_email, self.sender_password)\\n            server.sendmail(self.sender_email, recipient_email, msg.as_string())\\n            server.quit()\\n            print(f\\\"Email sent successfully to {recipient_email}\\\")\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            print(f\\\"Error sending email: {e}\\\")\\n\\n    def send_interview_invitation(self, recipient_email, candidate_name, interview_date, interview_time, interviewer_name, meeting_link):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Sends an interview invitation email to the candidate.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            recipient_email (str): The candidate's email address.\\n            candidate_name (str): The candidate's name.\\n            interview_date (str): The date of the interview (e.g., \\\"October 26, 2023\\\").\\n            interview_time (str): The time of the interview (e.g., \\\"10:00 AM\\\").\\n            interviewer_name (str): The name of the interviewer.\\n            meeting_link (str): The link to the online meeting.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = \\\"Interview Invitation\\\"\\n        body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nDear {candidate_name},\\n\\nWe are pleased to invite you to an interview for the position.\\n\\nDate: {interview_date}\\nTime: {interview_time}\\nInterviewer: {interviewer_name}\\nMeeting Link: {meeting_link}\\n\\nPlease be on time and prepared to discuss your qualifications and experience.\\n\\nWe look forward to meeting you.\\n\\nSincerely,\\nThe Hiring Team\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.send_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\n    def send_followup_email(self, recipient_email, candidate_name):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Sends a follow-up email to the candidate after the interview.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            recipient_email (str): The candidate's email address.\\n            candidate_name (str): The candidate's name.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = \\\"Following Up on Your Interview\\\"\\n        body = f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nDear {candidate_name},\\n\\nThank you for taking the time to interview with us. We appreciate you sharing your experience and qualifications.\\n\\nWe are currently reviewing all candidates and will be in touch soon with an update on your application status.\\n\\nSincerely,\\nThe Hiring Team\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.send_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage (Replace with your actual credentials and details)\\n    smtp_server = 'smtp.gmail.com'  # or your SMTP server\\n    port = 587  # or the appropriate port for your server\\n    sender_email = \\\"your_email@gmail.com\\\"  # Replace with your email\\n    sender_password = \\\"your_password\\\"  # Replace with your password (or app password)\\n\\n    email_notifier = EmailNotification(smtp_server, port, sender_email, sender_password)\\n\\n    # Example 1: Send interview invitation\\n    recipient_email = \\\"candidate_email@example.com\\\"  # Replace with the candidate's email\\n    candidate_name = \\\"John Doe\\\"\\n    interview_date = \\\"November 1, 2023\\\"\\n    interview_time = \\\"2:00 PM\\\"\\n    interviewer_name = \\\"Jane Smith\\\"\\n    meeting_link = \\\"https://meet.google.com/xyz\\\"\\n    email_notifier.send_interview_invitation(recipient_email, candidate_name, interview_date, interview_time, interviewer_name, meeting_link)\\n\\n    # Example 2: Send follow-up email\\n    email_notifier.send_followup_email(recipient_email, candidate_name)\\n```\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Develop scoring engine to evaluate and score candidate responses against predefined rubrics\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement response recording module to capture candidate answers during the technical interview\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nclass CandidateResponseRecorder:\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the CandidateResponseRecorder.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.responses = {}\\n\\n    def start_recording(self, candidate_name, question):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Starts recording the candidate's response to a specific question.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\\n            question (str): The question being asked.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if candidate_name not in self.responses:\\n            self.responses[candidate_name] = {}\\n        self.responses[candidate_name][question] = \\\"\\\"\\n        print(f\\\"Recording started for {candidate_name} on question: {question}\\\")\\n\\n    def record_response(self, candidate_name, question, response_chunk):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Records a chunk of the candidate's response.  Useful for streaming input.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\\n            question (str): The question being answered.\\n            response_chunk (str): A portion of the candidate's response.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if candidate_name in self.responses and question in self.responses[candidate_name]:\\n            self.responses[candidate_name][question] += response_chunk\\n        else:\\n            print(f\\\"Error: Recording not started for {candidate_name} on question: {question}\\\")\\n\\n    def stop_recording(self, candidate_name, question):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Stops recording the candidate's response.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\\n            question (str): The question being answered.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if candidate_name in self.responses and question in self.responses[candidate_name]:\\n            print(f\\\"Recording stopped for {candidate_name} on question: {question}\\\")\\n        else:\\n            print(f\\\"Error: Recording not started for {candidate_name} on question: {question}\\\")\\n\\n    def get_response(self, candidate_name, question):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Retrieves the recorded response for a given candidate and question.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\\n            question (str): The question to retrieve the response for.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            str: The candidate's response, or None if no response was recorded.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if candidate_name in self.responses and question in self.responses[candidate_name]:\\n            return self.responses[candidate_name][question]\\n        else:\\n            return None\\n\\n    def clear_response(self, candidate_name, question):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Clears the recorded response for a given candidate and question.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\\n            question (str): The question to clear the response for.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if candidate_name in self.responses and question in self.responses[candidate_name]:\\n            self.responses[candidate_name][question] = \\\"\\\"\\n            print(f\\\"Response cleared for {candidate_name} on question: {question}\\\")\\n        else:\\n            print(f\\\"Error: No response found for {candidate_name} on question: {question}\\\")\\n\\n    def get_all_responses(self, candidate_name):\\n      \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n      Retrieves all recorded responses for a given candidate.\\n\\n      Args:\\n          candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\\n\\n      Returns:\\n          dict: A dictionary of question-response pairs, or None if no responses were recorded for the candidate.\\n      \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n      if candidate_name in self.responses:\\n          return self.responses[candidate_name]\\n      else:\\n          return None\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    recorder = CandidateResponseRecorder()\\n\\n    candidate_name = \\\"Alice Smith\\\"\\n    question1 = \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\"\\n    question2 = \\\"What are decorators in Python and how are they used?\\\"\\n\\n    recorder.start_recording(candidate_name, question1)\\n    recorder.record_response(candidate_name, question1, \\\"Lists are mutable, \\\")\\n    recorder.record_response(candidate_name, question1, \\\"while tuples are immutable.\\\")\\n    recorder.stop_recording(candidate_name, question1)\\n\\n    recorder.start_recording(candidate_name, question2)\\n    recorder.record_response(candidate_name, question2, \\\"Decorators are a way to modify functions \\\")\\n    recorder.record_response(candidate_name, question2, \\\"in a clean and readable way.\\\")\\n    recorder.stop_recording(candidate_name, question2)\\n\\n    response1 = recorder.get_response(candidate_name, question1)\\n    print(f\\\"Alice's response to question 1: {response1}\\\")\\n\\n    response2 = recorder.get_response(candidate_name, question2)\\n    print(f\\\"Alice's response to question 2: {response2}\\\")\\n\\n    all_responses = recorder.get_all_responses(candidate_name)\\n    print(f\\\"All responses from Alice: {all_responses}\\\")\\n\\n    recorder.clear_response(candidate_name, question1)\\n    response1_after_clear = recorder.get_response(candidate_name, question1)\\n    print(f\\\"Alice's response to question 1 after clearing: {response1_after_clear}\\\")\\n```\\n\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-27T16:43:04.673269\"\n}"}
